==Middle English==
===Etymology 1===
{{dercat|enm|gem-pro|inh=1}}
From {{inh|enm|ang|gēotan}}, from {{inh|enm|gmw-pro|*geutan}}.
====Alternative forms====
* {{alter|enm|geten|yetten|ȝeten|ȝetten|ȝeoten|geoten}}
====Verb====
{{enm-verb|stem=yet|3=yet|4=yoten}}
# {{senseid|enm|to flow}} {{lb|enm|transitive}} To pour out from a container.
# {{lb|enm|intransitive}} To flow or gush.
# {{lb|enm|reflexive}} To [[overflow]].
# {{lb|enm|transitive|medicine}} To emit fluid from the body.
# {{lb|enm|transitive|figurative}} To send out, to send forth; to [[express]].
# {{lb|enm|transitive|medicine}} to administer medication by [[drop]] or [[injection]].
# {{lb|enm|transitive|chemistry}} To [[melt]] or [[soften]]; to [[dissolve]].
# {{lb|enm|transitive|smithing}} To [[cast]]; to [[found]].
# {{lb|enm|transitive}} To [[disperse]] or [[scatter]].
# {{lb|enm|transitive}} To take out for use; to [[brandish]].
